# Implementation Plan: AI-Scaffolded Observability Hackathon

This plan outlines the step-by-step approach to building a production-ready Web App with Full-Stack Observability, leveraging AI for rapid development.

## Review & Architectural Critique
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Configuration Pollution Critique:** Placing [Dockerfile](file:///d:/laragon/www/Saturday%20Session/Saturday%20Hackathon/backend/Dockerfile) in the project root is acceptable for MVPs, but for highly maintainable systems, we should isolate **Infrastructure concerns** from **Application logic**.
> - **Strict Decoupling:** Every service (Backend, Frontend) will have a dedicated `docker/` sub-directory for its [Dockerfile](file:///d:/laragon/www/Saturday%20Session/Saturday%20Hackathon/backend/Dockerfile) and service-specific OS/runtime configurations (FPM configs, Nginx templates).
> - **Orchestration Isolation:** The master [docker-compose.yml](file:///d:/laragon/www/Saturday%20Session/Saturday%20Hackathon/docker-compose.yml) will be moved to a separate orchestration layer to keep the root purely for project meta-files.
> - **Unified Ingress (Nginx):** Stays as the single entry point.

